Bryan Robson has recruited former  Manchester United and England colleague Viv Anderson as his assistant manager  at First Division Middlesbrough.
Robson, who took over as Ayresome Park boss last week, persuaded Anderson  to relinquish the manager's seat at fellow First Division club Barnsley after  only one season.
Anderson's assistant, the former Northern Ireland international, Danny  Wilson, has been appointed caretaker boss at Oakwell.
